A mother today joked that her wedding photographs might be used in evidence against her - after she defied a ruling to take her son out of school so that he could attend the ceremony.

Clare McLeary flouted the ruling by taking nine-year-old son Riley Bryant out of lessons so he could watch her tying the knot with fiance Andy McLeary, 37, on Lusty Gaze beach in Newquay, Cornwall.

Mrs McLeary, 30, who works as a police call handler, wrote to Clive Church of England School in Shrewsbury, Shropshire, asking for permission to let Riley miss three days this week.

